title: What Makes Great Music? French, English, Italian, Russian, Polish, Georgian, Jewish, Gospel, Baroque
description:
(Timestamps below!)
What makes for great music? Obviously there is no recipe. Which is exactly the problem with today's highly commercial pop music. And yet there is much we can discuss. This is my attempt to elucidate a few of aspects of music that I see that make it meaningful. 

What's what.
00:00:00 Introduction
00:04:10 About Holy Motors Intermission Music
00:06:03 Holy Motors Intermission Music
00:09:22 About Gospel quartets
00:11:05 Jubalaires - Noah
00:13:38 About June Tabor and English folk music
00:15:54 June Tabor - While the Gamekeeper Lies a-Sleeping
00:17:35 About English Country Dance Music
00:19:38 The Dressed Ship - St. George's Canzona
00:21:50 About Neotarantismo
00:24:07 Ballatti Tutti Quanti - Sponganese 
00:31:40 About UHOP gospel trombones
00:22:46 New York City street music players from the United House of Prayer
00:41:05 About Jordi Savall and Baroque dance music
00:44:13 Jordi Savall - La Folia
00:49:06 About Russian girls singing a folk song together
00:50:13 Russian girls on a train singing
00:52:58 About Tadeusz Wozniak and Polish music in the 1970s
00:54:04 Tadeusz Woźniak - Zegarmistrz światła
00:58:50 About Pelageya and Russian folk music
00:59:44 Pelageya - Under a green willow 
01:03:48 About Katell Keineg and how great music is buried by corporate pop music
01:05:15 Katell Keineg - There You Go
01:11:50 About Cantor Yosselle Rosenblatt 
01:14:47 Cantor Yosselle Rosenblatt - Ribono Shel Olom (Kaddish)
01:23:05 About Georgian Folk Music
01:25:05 Giorgi Ushikishvili - Orovela
01:28:16 Conclusions
